  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6653",
  "title": "Multi-Index Infinite Hits - Show More/Show Previous on refresh Bug",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nWhen I have multi index widgets and they have the infiniteHits widget, the bug occurs on those that aren't tied to the searchbox index.\n\nBug: On the second infiniteHits widget, When 'Show More Results' and 'Show Previous Results' are clickable, I click on 'Show More Results' and the results populate. I then click on 'Show Previous Results' and it'll take multiple clicks for the previous results to show up. the click count begins to increment where it starts playing catch up for each \"Show Previous/Show More\" button.\n \n\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\nTo recreate: on the second infiniteHits widget, \n\nClick show more results > \nrefresh the preview > \nclick show more results again > \nclick show previous results,  you have to click twice here >\nclick show more results, it will take 3 clicks here. The click count will keep going up for each button when following this pattern.\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/prod-meadow-dtnhyf?file=%2Fsrc%2Fapp.js\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nShow More Results and Show Previous Results should populate the results without needing multiple clicks. It should work like the first infiniteHits widget.\n\n### Package version\n\ninstantsearch.js 4.78.3\n\n### Operating system\n\nWindows 10\n\n### Browser\n\nChrome\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
